abstract: Zion Williamson rocks an orange stripe. Marcus Smart almost got fined over his socks. Some guys wear them on the wrong feet. (The wrong feet?)
snippet: Zion Williamson rocks an orange stripe. Marcus Smart almost got fined over his socks. Some guys wear them on the wrong feet. (The wrong feet?)
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Several years ago, Kevin Porter Jr., then a high school basketball star in Seattle, made a profound decision, one that would affect his life. He was creating his own team for the video game NBA 2K, and he decided to outfit one of the players in super long, over-the-calf socks.

abstract: The W.N.B.A.’s players and fans pushed furiously for Brittney Griner’s release from a Russian penal colony, but her plight also highlighted gender inequities in sports.
snippet: The W.N.B.A.’s players and fans pushed furiously for Brittney Griner’s release from a Russian penal colony, but her plight also highlighted gender inequities in sports.
lead_paragraph: Brittney Griner’s detention in Russia on drug charges could be described through the lens of war and politics, with Griner, one of the world’s best basketball players, a casualty of an international struggle between superpowers.

abstract: Iva Olivari and Ivancica Sudac have served Croatia’s federation since before it joined FIFA. They have had, in different ways, the job of a lifetime.
snippet: Iva Olivari and Ivancica Sudac have served Croatia’s federation since before it joined FIFA. They have had, in different ways, the job of a lifetime.
lead_paragraph: SPLIT, Croatia — The way the international soccer calendar is set up, Luka Modric is usually with his second family on his birthday in September. And it is always the same: A cake is made at Croatia’s training base and Modric, in his typically bashful style, blows out the candles as his teammates serenade him.

abstract: In his first news conference since his suspension began, before a game against the Memphis Grizzlies, Irving said he doesn’t stand for “anything close to hate speech or antisemitism.”
snippet: In his first news conference since his suspension began, before a game against the Memphis Grizzlies, Irving said he doesn’t stand for “anything close to hate speech or antisemitism.”
lead_paragraph: In his first game since being suspended for posting a link on social media to an antisemitic film, Nets guard Kyrie Irving shook off early rust to score 14 points  to help the Nets to a win, 127-115, against the Memphis Grizzlies in Brooklyn.

headline.main: Kyrie Irving Returns From Suspension
headline.print_headline: ‘A Moment in History I’m Going to Remember Forever’: Irving Is Reinstated

abstract: The Nets indicated Irving could potentially be available for Sunday’s game but have yet to officially announce the end of his suspension.
snippet: The Nets indicated Irving could potentially be available for Sunday’s game but have yet to officially announce the end of his suspension.
lead_paragraph: Nets guard Kyrie Irving, who has been suspended since Nov. 3, said during a television interview published on Saturday that he wanted to “apologize deeply” for his posting of a link to an antisemitic film.

abstract: The global appetites of Europe’s major leagues shape talent pipelines from South America to Africa. That picks winners and losers long before the games are played.
snippet: The global appetites of Europe’s major leagues shape talent pipelines from South America to Africa. That picks winners and losers long before the games are played.
lead_paragraph: SÃO PAULO, Brazil — Once a week, the boys from the Palmeiras youth academy climb aboard a bus and prepare for their regular visit to the past. These are the fledgling stars of Brazilian soccer: the best and brightest prospects from the most prolific youth system in the world’s greatest hothouse of talent.

abstract: Jonathan Greenblatt, the head of the Anti-Defamation League, was contacted by the Nets after Irving was suspended after highlighting an antisemitic film. On Thursday, Greenblatt said he had yet to speak with Irving directly.
snippet: Jonathan Greenblatt, the head of the Anti-Defamation League, was contacted by the Nets after Irving was suspended after highlighting an antisemitic film. On Thursday, Greenblatt said he had yet to speak with Irving directly.
lead_paragraph: When Jonathan Greenblatt, chief executive of the Anti-Defamation League, learned that Nets guard Kyrie Irving had posted a link on Twitter to an antisemitic film, he was touring a college with his son.

headline.print_headline: Jewish Leader Discusses the Issues  Around Irving and His Suspension

abstract: Irving’s antisemitic movie post is his biggest controversy yet. But the potential fallout could affect not just his basketball career but the N.B.A. itself.
snippet: Irving’s antisemitic movie post is his biggest controversy yet. But the potential fallout could affect not just his basketball career but the N.B.A. itself.
lead_paragraph: Before Kyrie Irving linked to an antisemitic film on Twitter, before he suggested that the Earth was flat or refused to get the Covid-19 vaccine, he had the weight of a city’s N.B.A. championship dreams tied to the flick of his wrist.

abstract: The Bruins are having their best recent season on the field, yet attendance is falling rapidly. Free tickets haven’t helped, and the athletic department’s balance sheet has suffered.
snippet: The Bruins are having their best recent season on the field, yet attendance is falling rapidly. Free tickets haven’t helped, and the athletic department’s balance sheet has suffered.
lead_paragraph: David Brownfield, who grew up a few bends in Sunset Boulevard from Westwood Village, could sing the U.C.L.A. fight song before he could shave. He graduated from U.C.L.A. in 1985 and has had football season tickets with friends ever since — even grudgingly paying what he calls the annual “extortion fee,” the $800 donation that was required for the privilege of buying his season tickets this year.

headline.print_headline: The Bruins Are Back. The Fans Are Not.

abstract: Irving, the Nets guard, met with Silver this week after promoting an antisemitic film on social media last month. Silver said Irving’s actions were damaging.
snippet: Irving, the Nets guard, met with Silver this week after promoting an antisemitic film on social media last month. Silver said Irving’s actions were damaging.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — N.B.A. Commissioner Adam Silver said Thursday that he didn’t believe Nets guard Kyrie Irving was antisemitic after meeting with him in person this week at the league’s headquarters in Manhattan. Irving has been facing backlash for promoting an antisemitic film on Twitter last month.

headline.print_headline: After a One-on-One Meeting, Silver Vouches for Irving

abstract: Female college athletes are making millions thanks to their large social media followings. But some who have fought for equity in women’s sports worry that their brand building is regressive.
snippet: Female college athletes are making millions thanks to their large social media followings. But some who have fought for equity in women’s sports worry that their brand building is regressive.
lead_paragraph: Olivia Dunne is a gymnast on Louisiana State’s women’s team.

abstract: Irving was suspended after he would not say he held no antisemitic beliefs. Nike suspended its relationship with him Friday.
snippet: Irving was suspended after he would not say he held no antisemitic beliefs. Nike suspended its relationship with him Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nets guard Kyrie Irving, who was suspended indefinitely in the fallout of his social media posts promoting an antisemitic film, will have to meet with Jewish leaders and with the team before he can return to play, General Manager Sean Marks said Friday.

headline.print_headline: Apology by Irving Isn’t Enough for His Suspension to End, Nets Say

abstract: Abdi Abdirahman will run his last competitive New York City Marathon on Sunday. Next year, he expects to return “with the masses, with a bunch of friends,” for the fun of it.
snippet: Abdi Abdirahman will run his last competitive New York City Marathon on Sunday. Next year, he expects to return “with the masses, with a bunch of friends,” for the fun of it.
lead_paragraph: There are so many stories about Abdi Abdirahman, the longtime bon vivant of American distance running.

abstract: Louisville received a handful of recruiting sanctions, a $5,000 fine and will be on probation for two years, but its former coach Rick Pitino received no penalties.
snippet: Louisville received a handful of recruiting sanctions, a $5,000 fine and will be on probation for two years, but its former coach Rick Pitino received no penalties.
lead_paragraph: In April 2019, in a downtown Manhattan courtroom, a video surreptitiously recorded inside a swank Las Vegas hotel suite offered a peek into how the world of college basketball recruiting works.

abstract: The star-loaded Nets have an awful record and parted ways with Coach Steve Nash. But a bigger problem with Kyrie Irving and his antisemitic social media post remains.
snippet: The star-loaded Nets have an awful record and parted ways with Coach Steve Nash. But a bigger problem with Kyrie Irving and his antisemitic social media post remains.
lead_paragraph: Be careful what you wish for. That adage comes to mind when I think of Kyrie Irving and his misguided, misinformed and downright dangerous support of antisemitism.

abstract: Injuries have hampered the N.B.A. career of the Pelicans’ Williamson, but a grueling summer of early morning workouts has him back on track.
snippet: Injuries have hampered the N.B.A. career of the Pelicans’ Williamson, but a grueling summer of early morning workouts has him back on track.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — At the start of the summer, as he waded into an off-season workout program that he hoped would build his body back into dynamic shape, Zion Williamson began setting his alarm for 4:30 a.m.

abstract: Hockey Canada has been criticized for its handling of accusations of sexual assault by players, as major sponsors and the federal government demand change.
snippet: Hockey Canada has been criticized for its handling of accusations of sexual assault by players, as major sponsors and the federal government demand change.
lead_paragraph: TORONTO — The sweeping changes at the top of Hockey Canada demanded for months by politicians, corporate sponsors, prominent figures in sport and the public finally happened Tuesday when Scott Smith stepped down as the organization’s president and chief executive. At the same time, the entire board of directors also resigned.

headline.print_headline: Hockey Canada C.E.O. And Board All Resign

abstract: Farah, a four-time Olympic gold medalist, dropped out of the London Marathon because of an injury. Is his competitive career reaching the finish line?
snippet: Farah, a four-time Olympic gold medalist, dropped out of the London Marathon because of an injury. Is his competitive career reaching the finish line?
lead_paragraph: It has been a running career of remarkable success and breadth and revelation: four Olympic gold medals won at 5,000 and 10,000 meters, a brave disclosure of being trafficked as a young boy, a knighthood conferred by Queen Elizabeth II — even a pose called the Mobot that celebrated the infectious joy with which Mo Farah of Britain prevailed.

abstract: Kipchoge ran the Berlin Marathon in a time of 2:01:09. Tigist Assefa shocked the women’s field by running her second marathon in 2:15:38, a course record.
snippet: Kipchoge ran the Berlin Marathon in a time of 2:01:09. Tigist Assefa shocked the women’s field by running her second marathon in 2:15:38, a course record.
lead_paragraph: Two questions come to mind any time Eliud Kipchoge toes the starting line of a marathon.

headline.main: Eliud Kipchoge Smashes His Own Marathon World Record
headline.print_headline: Kipchoge Smashes His Own World Record at the Berlin Marathon

abstract: Frank Shorter couldn’t have imagined the impact his 1972 Olympic marathon victory would have on the sport. “I was just a piece in the puzzle,” he said.
snippet: Frank Shorter couldn’t have imagined the impact his 1972 Olympic marathon victory would have on the sport. “I was just a piece in the puzzle,” he said.
lead_paragraph: For people who favor clean and simple marks for the start of something new, America’s “running boom” began 50 years ago today, on Sept. 10, 1972, when Frank Shorter, a Yale graduate and law student at the University of Florida, won the marathon at the Munich Olympics.

headline.main: How a Marathon Win 50 Years Ago Kick-Started the ‘Running Boom’
headline.print_headline: Fifty Years Ago, a Marathon Gold Medal Kick-Started America’s ‘Running Boom’

abstract: The university’s football players nearly skipped their opening game in protest of their mismanaged athletic department. Recent history shows far more dysfunction within the university’s sports program.
snippet: The university’s football players nearly skipped their opening game in protest of their mismanaged athletic department. Recent history shows far more dysfunction within the university’s sports program.
lead_paragraph: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — Here’s what comes with being a football player at Florida A&M: getting booted from the dorms during training camp and sleeping in your car. Bad or uncertain advice from an overwhelmed staff about what classes to sign up for. Monthslong waits for the scholarship check that covers your meals and rent.

abstract: Bird, 41, the Seattle Storm guard, had said she would retire after this season. The Storm fell to the Las Vegas Aces in the W.N.B.A. semifinals on Tuesday.
snippet: Bird, 41, the Seattle Storm guard, had said she would retire after this season. The Storm fell to the Las Vegas Aces in the W.N.B.A. semifinals on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Seattle Storm fans wanted one more year. Sue Bird gave it to them.

headline.main: Sue Bird Sheds ‘Happy Tears’ as She Ends W.N.B.A. Career
headline.print_headline: Four Championships and One Encore Later, Bird Calls It a Career

abstract: In a rare interview, the French soccer star discussed chasing the Champions League title, supplanting his teammate Lionel Messi as world player of the year and the possibility of a move to Real Madrid.
snippet: In a rare interview, the French soccer star discussed chasing the Champions League title, supplanting his teammate Lionel Messi as world player of the year and the possibility of a move to Real Madrid.
lead_paragraph: Kylian Mbappé will eventually turn up for his interview in an oversized vehicle outfitted with tinted windows, and accompanied by his mother, two P.R. reps, two lawyers, a small documentary crew, a stylist and a friend whose role is, initially, unclear. This is how one of the world’s biggest sports stars travels these days. Kylian Mbappé doesn’t just walk through the door. He arrives.

abstract: At the U.S. Open, Serena Williams laughed, rocked sparkly shoes, rang the bell at the stock exchange, beat two opponents, teared up and said goodbye. She didn’t win, but she didn’t lose.
snippet: At the U.S. Open, Serena Williams laughed, rocked sparkly shoes, rang the bell at the stock exchange, beat two opponents, teared up and said goodbye. She didn’t win, but she didn’t lose.
lead_paragraph: Serena Williams left the Lotte New York Palace hotel on Madison Avenue and folded herself into the back seat of a dark green Lincoln Navigator. She arrived at the Billie Jean King National Tennis Center about 15 minutes later. Traffic’s bearable on Saturday mornings.

abstract: Long-distance relay races bring together an eclectic group of runners in road racing’s equivalent of Van Life.
snippet: Long-distance relay races bring together an eclectic group of runners in road racing’s equivalent of Van Life.
lead_paragraph: HINCKLEY, Minn. — Just after 9 p.m., a noticeable quiet descended on the van full of sweaty athletes who had been running and driving for 13 hours. We weren’t even halfway through our roughly 200-mile relay race, and the sun was already setting as we dug out our headlamps and reflective gear.

abstract: “I’m just trying to get the hang of everything,” said Jamad Fiin, whose talents have upset people’s expectations of what a girl in a hijab can do.
snippet: “I’m just trying to get the hang of everything,” said Jamad Fiin, whose talents have upset people’s expectations of what a girl in a hijab can do.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — When Jamad Fiin notched her millionth follower on Instagram a few months ago, her friends bought her a batch of celebratory cupcakes.

abstract: Coaches recruiting the high school point guard known as Bronny will have a lot to navigate, including his famous father’s ties to Nike, ESPN and the state of Ohio.
snippet: Coaches recruiting the high school point guard known as Bronny will have a lot to navigate, including his famous father’s ties to Nike, ESPN and the state of Ohio.
lead_paragraph: NORTH AUGUSTA, S.C. — As LeBron James sat on a folding chair in the corner of a recreation-center basketball court last week, he often appeared to be in a state of agita.

abstract: Some have referred to this era as a golden age of better and better times. But a deeper look at the data shows the simple shorthand conclusion is incomplete.
snippet: Some have referred to this era as a golden age of better and better times. But a deeper look at the data shows the simple shorthand conclusion is incomplete.
lead_paragraph: The highlight of the track and field world championships, which wrapped up in Eugene, Ore., on Sunday, was undoubtedly Sydney McLaughlin’s shattering her own world record, and the rest of the field, in the 400-meter hurdles. It was a record set in dominant fashion, the type of performance fans watch sports for but rarely actually get to see.

abstract: Now that college athletes can profit from their fame, some University of Oregon runners are getting paid to help visitors staying in town for the track and field world championships.
snippet: Now that college athletes can profit from their fame, some University of Oregon runners are getting paid to help visitors staying in town for the track and field world championships.
lead_paragraph: As the track and field world championships made their first appearance in the U.S. at Hayward Field in Eugene, Ore., this month, some University of Oregon athletes decided to creatively capitalize on their fame and the lack of abundant housing in this quaint college town.

headline.main: Oregon athletes find a creative way to make money: Housing rentals.

abstract: Distance running is a relentlessly individual sport. But professional running teams, and their polished Instagram accounts, are upending that dynamic.
snippet: Distance running is a relentlessly individual sport. But professional running teams, and their polished Instagram accounts, are upending that dynamic.
lead_paragraph: At the track and field world championships, distance runners compete on behalf of their countries. What’s less visible to the average fan is that most are also competing for their shoe company sponsors, which largely provide the funding that makes track and field a viable career. Even less visible to the average fan — especially if you aren’t on Instagram — is that a growing number of them are competing on behalf of professional running teams.

headline.main: Representing a Nation on TV, and a Running Team on Instagram
headline.print_headline: With Teams Surging In Popularity, Running Isn’t Lonely Anymore

abstract: Warholm, the world-record holder, appeared to be in control much of the race. But it was Dos Santos who was able to find another gear in the final straight away.
snippet: Warholm, the world-record holder, appeared to be in control much of the race. But it was Dos Santos who was able to find another gear in the final straight away.
lead_paragraph: Alison dos Santos of Brazil upset Karsten Warholm, the star quarter-mile hurdler from Norway, and Warholm’s chief rival, Rai Benjamin of the United States, throwing a major curveball in the rematch of one of the great races of last year’s Olympics.

headline.main: Alison dos Santos upset Karsten Warholm in the 400-meter hurdles.

abstract: Karsten Warholm, the Norwegian reigning world champion and gold medalist in the 400-meter hurdles has a budding rivalry with the American Rai Benjamin. It’s just what track and field needs.
snippet: Karsten Warholm, the Norwegian reigning world champion and gold medalist in the 400-meter hurdles has a budding rivalry with the American Rai Benjamin. It’s just what track and field needs.
lead_paragraph: Karsten Warholm remembers two things about the moment everything changed — in that magical race, in his career and in his life.

abstract: Galen Rupp is the greatest American distance runner of his generation. For a long time, the disgraced coach Alberto Salazar guided him. Should that matter?

lead_paragraph: Galen Rupp is the greatest American distance runner of the 21st century.

headline.main: Can Galen Rupp outrun the shadow of a disgraced former coach?

abstract: Eugene, Ore., has spent more than a century evolving into “TrackTown.” On Friday, the World Athletics Championships opened in this unlikely destination.
snippet: Eugene, Ore., has spent more than a century evolving into “TrackTown.” On Friday, the World Athletics Championships opened in this unlikely destination.
lead_paragraph: World championships in track and field generally take place in world capitals. Rome, Beijing, Moscow, Paris and London have all taken a turn hosting the biggest event in the sport other than the Olympic Games.

headline.print_headline: History and Nike Both Helped Lure the World’s Biggest Track Meet to Oregon

abstract: Teams usually fly on commercial airlines, but that will change for the W.N.B.A. finals. This could be good news for players’ health, finances and game.
snippet: Teams usually fly on commercial airlines, but that will change for the W.N.B.A. finals. This could be good news for players’ health, finances and game.
lead_paragraph: Delay after delay. Then, a cancellation. Germy bathrooms. Wrestling with yourself over paying $4 for a small bag of Skittles. Forgetting your headphones and wanting to cry. Now, the power plug at your seat is not working, and the people sitting next to you on the airplane won’t stop coughing. Do they have Covid?

abstract: Forty-four years ago, Henry Rono set multiple world records on the track. Much of his life was later overshadowed by addiction. But at 70, he has no regrets.
snippet: Forty-four years ago, Henry Rono set multiple world records on the track. Much of his life was later overshadowed by addiction. But at 70, he has no regrets.
lead_paragraph: KIPTARAGON, Kenya — One afternoon in May, as a cold rain pelted the roof of his brother’s rural home, Henry Rono sipped a mug of tea and reflected on what he called his greatest achievement.

headline.main: The Most Talented Runner of His Generation Takes the Unexpected Route Back Home
headline.print_headline: A Path of Success, Then a Winding Journey

abstract: Xavier Booker, in an unusual move, is sidestepping the carnival of tournaments put on by shoe companies to showcase elite men’s basketball players.
snippet: Xavier Booker, in an unusual move, is sidestepping the carnival of tournaments put on by shoe companies to showcase elite men’s basketball players.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Few could have foreseen Xavier Booker, who as a sophomore barely got off his high school team’s bench, in his current position: being scrutinized by N.B.A. scouts and recruited by Kansas, Kentucky, Gonzaga, Duke, Michigan State, Michigan, Indiana and a cadre of others.

abstract: Advances in physical preparation keep their bodies in the game, and so can the changing nature of sports business and celebrity.
snippet: Advances in physical preparation keep their bodies in the game, and so can the changing nature of sports business and celebrity.
lead_paragraph: WIMBLEDON, England — Most tennis professionals are retired by their mid-30s. But last week, there was Serena Williams, at almost 41, grinding against a competitor a little more than half her age for more than three hours at Wimbledon.

abstract: Courts in Russia heavily favor the prosecution, experts said, pointing to a prisoner swap as perhaps the W.N.B.A. star’s best chance to come home.
snippet: Courts in Russia heavily favor the prosecution, experts said, pointing to a prisoner swap as perhaps the W.N.B.A. star’s best chance to come home.
lead_paragraph: More than four months after she was first detained, the W.N.B.A. star Brittney Griner is expected to appear in a Russian courtroom on Friday for the start of a trial on drug charges that legal experts said was all but certain to end in a conviction despite the clamor in the United States for her release.

abstract: Devon Allen is one of the best hurdlers in the world. He’ll soon shift his focus to N.F.L. training camp.
snippet: Devon Allen is one of the best hurdlers in the world. He’ll soon shift his focus to N.F.L. training camp.
lead_paragraph: Last month, Devon Allen ran the third-fastest time in the history of the 110-meter hurdles.

abstract: Young prospects in men’s basketball have numerous ways to impress college coaches (and options to bypass them). But the way coaches are looking for new talent has changed, too.
snippet: Young prospects in men’s basketball have numerous ways to impress college coaches (and options to bypass them). But the way coaches are looking for new talent has changed, too.
lead_paragraph: BLAIRSTOWN, N.J. — Three days after traveling from his family’s vacation home in Porto Heli, Greece, Symeon Efstathiou found himself in a basketball gym at a remote boarding school tucked away in the northwest corner of New Jersey.

headline.print_headline: Recruiting Trail Reflects a Shifting Game

abstract: Three top draft prospects — Paolo Banchero, Chet Holmgren and Jalen Williams — explained their approach to fashion. “I feel like I don’t really miss when I put fits on,” Holmgren said.
snippet: Three top draft prospects — Paolo Banchero, Chet Holmgren and Jalen Williams — explained their approach to fashion. “I feel like I don’t really miss when I put fits on,” Holmgren said.
lead_paragraph: Paolo Banchero lifted the right sleeve of his black hooded sweatshirt to point out the green tattoo ink on his forearm. His long arms make up most of the 7-foot-1 wingspan that positioned him as one of the top prospects in the N.B.A. draft on Thursday, but they also tell a story.

headline.main: Allyson Felix’s Retirement Plan Has Already Started

abstract: Fans may have heard of Chet Holmgren and Shaedon Sharpe, but others are ready for their shot: “I knew if I got good enough, the N.B.A. would find me,” one said.
snippet: Fans may have heard of Chet Holmgren and Shaedon Sharpe, but others are ready for their shot: “I knew if I got good enough, the N.B.A. would find me,” one said.
lead_paragraph: When the Orlando Magic hand their draft card to N.B.A. Commissioner Adam Silver, on Thursday night at Barclays Center, they’ll settle a debate that has raged in draft circles for the better part of a year: Who should be the No. 1 pick?

headline.main: N.B.A. Draft Preview: A Deep Field Could Yield Surprise Stars
headline.print_headline: Surprise Stars Lurk in a Year Deep With Talent

abstract: The former Duke center Mark Williams is expected to be picked at the N.B.A. draft this week. He’s quickly learning what going pro really means.
snippet: The former Duke center Mark Williams is expected to be picked at the N.B.A. draft this week. He’s quickly learning what going pro really means.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — The training drill is named after LeBron James. Most people would be better off if they just let him do it.

abstract: Fine art inspired by the sport is everywhere. One gallery filled nearly 5,000 square feet, and its curator said she “could do a Part 2 and Part 3 because there is that much work out there.”
snippet: Fine art inspired by the sport is everywhere. One gallery filled nearly 5,000 square feet, and its curator said she “could do a Part 2 and Part 3 because there is that much work out there.”
lead_paragraph: The basketballs are deflated, doused in spray paint or covered in 24-karat gold leaf. They’re sculpted from porcelain, plopped in cement or layered into enormous pyramids. They’re splashed onto canvases, carved into cheeky jack-o’-lanterns, flattened out like flower petals.

headline.print_headline: From the Court To the Art Gallery

abstract: Failure to qualify for Qatar has condemned Nigeria to a humbling summer instead of months of World Cup hype. Then there’s the fate of its famous jersey.
snippet: Failure to qualify for Qatar has condemned Nigeria to a humbling summer instead of months of World Cup hype. Then there’s the fate of its famous jersey.
lead_paragraph: In those initial moments of agony in March after Nigeria was eliminated from qualification for this year’s World Cup, the most immediate thoughts of Amaju Pinnick, the president of Nigeria’s soccer federation, were of the disappointment being felt by his 200 million countrymen in Africa’s most populous nation.

headline.main: Tallying the Costs, Shirts and All, of Missing the World Cup
headline.print_headline: Dashed Hopes and Unsold Shirts:  The Costs of Missing the World Cup

abstract: The bid by Knight and Alan Smolinisky, a part owner of the Dodgers, tops $2 billion, according to people familiar with their proposal.
snippet: The bid by Knight and Alan Smolinisky, a part owner of the Dodgers, tops $2 billion, according to people familiar with their proposal.
lead_paragraph: Phil Knight, a founder of the athletic apparel company Nike, and Alan Smolinisky, an entrepreneur and part owner of the Los Angeles Dodgers, have submitted a bid to purchase the Portland Trail Blazers, according to people familiar with their bid.

abstract: The demise of a relationship that produced one of the most popular games of all time will mean risks for soccer’s governing body but few changes for consumers.
snippet: The demise of a relationship that produced one of the most popular games of all time will mean risks for soccer’s governing body but few changes for consumers.
lead_paragraph: After almost three decades, one of the most successful commercial relationships in sports is over.

abstract: Boston Celtics Coach Ime Udoka struggled to catch on in the N.B.A. as a player. But once he did, he leveraged his experience to become a leader on the sideline.
snippet: Boston Celtics Coach Ime Udoka struggled to catch on in the N.B.A. as a player. But once he did, he leveraged his experience to become a leader on the sideline.
lead_paragraph: Follow our live coverage of the 2022 N.B.A. Finals between Golden State and the Boston Celtics.

headline.main: An N.B.A. Coach’s Journey from FedEx to the Top Job
headline.print_headline: From Loading Trucks for FedEx  To Calling Shots for the Celtics

abstract: The search for elite players is so competitive that IMG, the agency that once ruled tennis, is cultivating preteens to find the next prodigy, giving them access to representatives from the pro tours and Nike.
snippet: The search for elite players is so competitive that IMG, the agency that once ruled tennis, is cultivating preteens to find the next prodigy, giving them access to representatives from the pro tours and Nike.
lead_paragraph: ACHARNES, Greece — Behold Dominik Defoe. Ten years old and barely taller than the net. Golden brown shoulder-length curls bouncing in the air as he chases and crushes tennis balls, which he does better than just about any kid his age.

abstract: Markelle Taylor started running as an antidote to despair. This week he ran the Boston Marathon as a free man, with a time of 2:52:00.
snippet: Markelle Taylor started running as an antidote to despair. This week he ran the Boston Marathon as a free man, with a time of 2:52:00.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Out of all the runners in the first wave of the Boston Marathon on Monday, there was one lean, muscular marathoner with skinny ankles from Northern California for whom all the nervous energy had profound significance. Markelle Taylor, a former lifer at San Quentin State Prison, was running free for the first time.

abstract: France’s soccer federation forbids hijab-wearing women from competing in soccer games, even though FIFA allows them. A collective of Muslim players is fighting what it considers a discriminatory rule.
snippet: France’s soccer federation forbids hijab-wearing women from competing in soccer games, even though FIFA allows them. A collective of Muslim players is fighting what it considers a discriminatory rule.
lead_paragraph: SARCELLES, France — Every time Mama Diakité heads to a soccer game, her stomach is in knots.

abstract: If you’ve seen golf shoes on the street, it is because one of the world’s most conservative sports has been getting a fresh look on the course.
snippet: If you’ve seen golf shoes on the street, it is because one of the world’s most conservative sports has been getting a fresh look on the course.
lead_paragraph: Streetwear — long the provenance of New York hip-hop and California surf culture — has been making its way to the green grass of golf courses.

headline.main: Golf Shoes Meet Streetwear and Sneaker Culture
headline.print_headline: Sneakers and Golf Finally Discover Each Other

abstract: With 1.2 million Twitter followers and a new show debuting Monday, the former N.B.A. player appears to have an enviable life. But he’s haunted by what happened the last time he was famous.
snippet: With 1.2 million Twitter followers and a new show debuting Monday, the former N.B.A. player appears to have an enviable life. But he’s haunted by what happened the last time he was famous.
lead_paragraph: Sitting in a Midtown Manhattan cafe after shooting B-roll for his new show on CNN+, Rex Chapman says he knows that he’s living a dream, and it’s making him uncomfortable. “I struggle with it,” he said.

headline.main: Rex Chapman Isn’t Sure He Deserves Good Things
headline.print_headline: Living a Dream He’s Not Certain He Deserves

abstract: As teams snatch up quarterbacks in free agency, Kaepernick has been quickly organizing workouts around the country and posting them to social media.
snippet: As teams snatch up quarterbacks in free agency, Kaepernick has been quickly organizing workouts around the country and posting them to social media.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — In the five years since he last played in an N.F.L. game, Colin Kaepernick, the former San Francisco 49ers quarterback who ignited an international debate on athletes’ right to protest, has only sporadically surfaced in public. Accepting an award here, or rolling out a Netflix series there, Kaepernick has in those calculated appearances always affirmed that he was “staying ready” for a return to football.

abstract: Enes Kanter Freedom has condemned human rights abuses in Turkey for years. Now he claims the N.B.A. is blackballing him as he focuses on abuses in China.
snippet: Enes Kanter Freedom has condemned human rights abuses in Turkey for years. Now he claims the N.B.A. is blackballing him as he focuses on abuses in China.
lead_paragraph: “My activism actually started when I was 9 years old,” Enes Kanter Freedom told a rapt audience of pro-democracy activists that included Garry Kasparov, the former world chess champion known for his opposition to President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia.

abstract: The New York City Half Marathon is scheduled to be run on Sunday for the first time in three years, and a number of prominent names will be at the starting line.
snippet: The New York City Half Marathon is scheduled to be run on Sunday for the first time in three years, and a number of prominent names will be at the starting line.
lead_paragraph: Last December, Sam Grotewold, who leads the professional running program at New York Road Runners, started scratching out a list of people he hoped to lure to the New York City Half Marathon.

abstract: Griner, one of the world’s best basketball players, was detained in Russia on what customs officials described as drug charges. Fans are worried.

abstract: Cathy Engelbert, the league’s commissioner, said the investment could help fund marketing, improve digital products and fan outreach to increase revenue.

lead_paragraph: The W.N.B.A. has raised $75 million from more than two dozen investors in a bid to revamp its business model as players call for expansion, higher salaries and better benefits.

abstract: After a two-year search, the team announced a new name and mascot to replace the generic moniker it adopted to replace the longtime name, which was considered a racial slur of Native Americans.

lead_paragraph: Washington, meet the Commanders.

abstract: An arbitrator’s ruling, revealed for the first time, shows that allegations of physical assault prompted a lifetime ban for Alberto Salazar, the former coach of the Nike Oregon Project.
snippet: An arbitrator’s ruling, revealed for the first time, shows that allegations of physical assault prompted a lifetime ban for Alberto Salazar, the former coach of the Nike Oregon Project.
lead_paragraph: The famed running coach Alberto Salazar, who helped top Americans be more competitive in track and field before he was suspended for doping violations, was barred from the sport for life last month after an arbitrator found that he more likely than not had sexually assaulted an athlete on two different occasions, according to a summary of the ruling reviewed by The New York Times.

abstract: A woman accused the young English forward of assaulting her in a post on Instagram. The team said he would not play or train “until further notice.”
snippet: A woman accused the young English forward of assaulting her in a post on Instagram. The team said he would not play or train “until further notice.”
lead_paragraph: Manchester United said it had suspended its young forward Mason Greenwood and would bar him from playing matches or even training with his teammates after he was accused by a woman on Sunday of assaulting her. The woman made the claim in a post on her personal social media account that included images, video and an audio recording.

abstract: A former Nike marketing executive turned mind-set coach is guiding the biggest stars at the Australian Open through the crucible of competition and fame.
snippet: A former Nike marketing executive turned mind-set coach is guiding the biggest stars at the Australian Open through the crucible of competition and fame.
lead_paragraph: Some of the most important moments of this year’s Australian Open took place far from a tennis court and had nothing to do with a certain vaccine-averse Serbian champion.

abstract: On Sunday, two mothers in their late 30s set new American records in the marathon and the half marathon. It’s a sign of things to come.
snippet: On Sunday, two mothers in their late 30s set new American records in the marathon and the half marathon. It’s a sign of things to come.
lead_paragraph: Keira D’Amato and Sara Hall are still processing what happened Sunday.

headline.main: Keira D’Amato and Sara Hall Rewrite the Distance Running History Books

abstract: Despite being a Grand Slam champion herself, Raducanu had never faced one until she played and defeated Stephens in the first round of the Australian Open.
snippet: Despite being a Grand Slam champion herself, Raducanu had never faced one until she played and defeated Stephens in the first round of the Australian Open.
lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia — Emma Raducanu wasted no time in announcing her presence in her first Grand Slam match since her stunning run to last year’s U.S. Open title.

headline.print_headline: After a Slump, Raducanu Makes a Statement

abstract: Barbara Mack hugged Larry Miller after he apologized for killing her brother, Edward David White. But if she were 30 years younger, she told him, “I would have been across that table at you.”
snippet: Barbara Mack hugged Larry Miller after he apologized for killing her brother, Edward David White. But if she were 30 years younger, she told him, “I would have been across that table at you.”
lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — Barbara Mack lives a block from the corner where her teenage brother was shot to death while on his way home from work on Sept. 30, 1965. Hasan Adams was only 8 months old when the bullet took his father. Azizah Arline was months from being born and never met her dad. More than half a century later, they have finally received an apology from, and discussed restitution with, the man who committed the murder.

abstract: With improved accessibility and support from the government, skateboarding schools, stores and a diverse social scene have taken flight.
snippet: With improved accessibility and support from the government, skateboarding schools, stores and a diverse social scene have taken flight.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — One year ago, Carolina Altamirano left her home in Oaxaca City, Mexico, where she had been skateboarding for nine years, in search of opportunities to grow her skateboarding career.
